sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: TetR
sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:description: Tet operator repressor. Binds to the TetO operator (see P12m, P15m) as a tetramer, blocking transcription from the associated promoter. Repression is lifted by binding to tetracycline or its derivative anhydrotetracycline (aTc). Contains no degradation tags (unlike C2d).

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:description: Promoter regulated by the engineered repressor LacI (C1d or C63m) or its engineered variant LacI-M (C72m). Has low cross-talk when used with other members of the Marionette system when used with C72m. Constitutively active, and is repressed »500x by C1d, C63m, or C72m when the repressor is not complexed with Isopropyl-B-D-thiogalactiside (IPTG).
